FT  03 APR 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Have printer, will travel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The archetypal travelling salesman on the road with a portable computer
often requires printing facilities, but all too often portability results in
lower quality and reduced convenience.
Now Kodak has launched the Diconix 701, a lightweight ink-jet printer which
it claims offers high flexibility for anyone needing a printer on the run.
The 701 weighs less than 6lbs, operates from battery or mains and is priced
at Pounds 429 plus VAT. Kodak: UK, 0442 61122.
