<TEXT>
BT yesterday promised to 'put customers first' as it announced improved
service initiatives on the first anniversary of the telecommunications
group's reorganisation, Michiyo Nakamoto writes.
Extended opening hours, from 8am to 6pm, simplified contact numbers for
inquiries and a faster, more efficient complaints-handling system are
planned.
BT will also guarantee prompt installation and fault repair in a
customer-service guarantee programme. If it fails to install a line by the
agreed date or repair a fault by the end of the next working day after it is
reported, residential customers will be able to claim a month's network
rental for every extra day they wait. Business customers will be able to
claim Pounds 25 a day.
