practices, export incentives and subsidies.
Senator Evans said the US had been told 'vigorously' that the allegations
were denied by Australia, which has substantially reduced tariff protection
over the last decade.
He said many US trade practices were 'unquestionably unfair,' especially in
areas such as agriculture which were of crucial importance to Australian
exporters.
