<TEXT>
THE president of Venezuela's central bank, Mr Miguel Rodriguez, has resigned
in an effort to ease political pressure on the beleagured government of
President Carlos Andres Perez.
He named, late on Wednesday, Ms Ruth de Krivoy, a respected economist and
the first woman to hold the job, to head the central bank.
