<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 92 / Shake-up at Royal Mail is completed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DIANE SUMMERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ROYAL MAIL, the letters arm of the Post Office, yesterday completed a
reorganisation which has cut management and administrative staff by 3,500
and forced a further 9,000 managers to re-apply for their jobs, Diane
Summers writes.
The number of reporting levels between the managing director and the postal
worker delivering letters has been cut from nine to six.
Headquarters staff have been reduced from about 2,000 to 160. The shake-up
will result in annual savings of Pounds 60m to Pounds 70m. Nine divisions,
each with average turnover of Pounds 300m, have replaced four territories
and 64 districts.
</TEXT>
