Labour's Sheffield rally was brilliant, superb. It far surpassed anything
that the Conservatives could have managed. It electrified the party's
supporters and came across wonderfully on television. No that wasn't the
judgment of Neil Kinnock's spin doctors. It was offered by Harvey Thomas.
