<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Australian wool has sold at steady prices this week, but the previous easier
tendency has not been replaced by a definitely firmer movement. A high
proportion of auction offerings is still being withdrawn by farmers hoping
for better prices later on. The lack of demand from the old Soviet Union
areas, and patchy participation from Eastern Europe, continue to act as a
major depressing influence. Other major wool-using countries were active
buyers during February's price rise but are less keen after the recent
market setback. The AWC market indicator rose 2 cents to 572 on April 1.
