FT  02 APR 92 / The Lex Column: Mountleigh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The revolving door continues to spin at Mountleigh, a property company in
rather more urgent need of revolving credit. Mr Steven Gerard, the new chief
executive, is not a bank appointee. But as a former senior executive at
Citibank, one of Mountleigh's main lenders, he looks suspiciously like the
next best thing.
Somewhat unnervingly for investors, Mr Gerard felt compelled to mark his
appointment yesterday by promising a strategically focused operating and
financial plan 'which will be satisfactory to all creditors'. He also
undertook to maximise value for shareholders. In this regard, he could begin
by updating them on progress made so far in completing the Pounds 125m sale
of the Merry Hill shopping centre, first announced in January. No news is
not necessarily good news.
