   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SENIOR Tory figure in the north-west has made a coded attack on
Conservative Central Office over the party's election campaign, Ian Hamilton
Fazey writes.
Mr Andrew Pearce, who is fighting the marginal seat of Ellesmere Port and
Neston, said yesterday that candidates were looking for 'some zing and zap'
